Database application
Dmitry Korolev, Computer Science Center, 2013

In order to build project 'Database', print:
mvn package
In order to run server, print:
java -jar DatabaseServer/target/DatabaseServer-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar {args}
In order to run client, print:
java -jar DatabaseClient/target/DatabaseClient-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar {args}
In order to run balancer, print:
java -jar DatabaseBalancer/target/DatabaseBalancer-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar {args}

In order to know about all {args} please see README

!!!!FR1!!!!
To generate initial big data you can use next command:
--run server
java -jar DatabaseServer/target/DatabaseServer-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar --port 1107 --mode combined --directory . --split-rate 10 --memory-max-size 104857600
--run balancer
java -jar DatabaseBalancer/target/DatabaseBalancer-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar --port 1111
--run client
java -jar DatabaseClient/target/DatabaseClient-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar --list-of-servers localhost:1111
add_server "localhost:1107" master

!!!!FR2!!!!
--run server 1
java -jar DatabaseServer/target/DatabaseServer-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar --port 1107 --mode memory
--run server 2
java -jar DatabaseServer/target/DatabaseServer-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar --port 1108 --mode memory
--run balancer
java -jar DatabaseBalancer/target/DatabaseBalancer-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar --port 1111
--run client
java -jar DatabaseClient/target/DatabaseClient-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar --list-of-servers localhost:1111
add_server "localhost:1107" master
add_server "localhost:1108" master

